And Jesus, perceiving the thought of their heart, took a little child and set him by Him,
and said to them, <FR>“Whoever receives this little child in My name receives Me; and whoever receives Me receives Him who sent Me. Because he who is least among you all, they will be great.”<Fr>
Now John responded and said, “Master, we saw someone casting out demons in Your name, and we forbade him because he does not follow with us.”
But Jesus said to him, <FR>“Do not forbid <FI>him<Fi>, because he who is not against us is for us.”<Fr>
Now it came to pass, when the time had come for Him to be received up, that He steadfastly set His face to go to Jerusalem,
