And Jesus answered and said to her, <FR>“Martha, Martha, you are worried and troubled about many things.<Fr>
<FR>But one thing is needed, and Mary has chosen that good part, which will not be taken away from her.”<Fr>
Now it came to pass, as He was praying in a certain place, when He ceased, that one of His disciples said to Him, “Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.”
So He said to them, <FR>“When you pray, say: Our Father who is in heaven, Hallowed be Your name. Your kingdom come. Your will be done as in heaven, so <FI>also <Fi>on earth.<Fr>
