He also said to His disciples: <FR>“There was a certain rich man who had a steward, and an accusation was brought to him that this man was wasting his goods.<Fr>
<FR>So he called him and said to him, ‘What is this I hear about you? Give an account of your stewardship, because you can no longer be steward.'<Fr>
<FR>“Then the steward said within himself, ‘What shall I do? Because, my master is taking the stewardship away from me. I cannot dig; I am ashamed to beg.<Fr>
