One of His disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, said to Him,
“There is a boy here who has five barley loaves and two small fish, but what are they among so many?”
Then Jesus said, <FR>“Make the men sit down.” <Fr>Now there was a lot of grass in the place. So the men sat down, in number about five thousand.
