Then those who heard it, being convicted by <FI>their own<Fi> conscience, went out one by one, beginning with the oldest <FI>even<Fi> to the last. And Jesus was left alone, and the woman standing in the midst.
When Jesus had lifted Himself up and saw no one but the woman, He said to her, <FR>“Woman, where are those accusers of yours? Has no one condemned you?”<Fr>
