Then the Jews replied and said to Him, “Do we not say rightly that You are a Samaritan and have a demon?”
Jesus answered, <FR>“I do not have a demon; but I honor My Father, and you dishonor Me.<Fr>
<FR>And I do not seek My own glory; there is One who seeks and judges.<Fr>
<FR>Truly, truly, I say to you, if anyone keeps My word he will never see death.”<Fr>
Then the Jews said to Him, “Now we know that You have a demon! Abraham is dead, and the prophets; and You say, ‘If anyone keeps My word he will never taste death.'
